# Vision app rules

- Use the `libreyolo-web` high-level API (`loadModel`, `predict`, `BoxOverlay`,
  `listModels`). Do not hand-roll ONNX pre/post-processing unless a model isn't
  supported.
- Detection runs per-frame in a `requestAnimationFrame` loop. Keep per-frame work
  cheap; offload anything heavy to a Web Worker.
- The overlay canvas dimensions must match `video.videoWidth/Height` so box
  coordinates align with the feed.
- WebGPU is preferred; assume WASM fallback exists. Don't assume a GPU.
- Camera access needs a secure context — test on localhost or https.
